 COMMENTS:
 --------              

These are three films made 11 years apart which are probably the most lovable fantasies ever made. Its not really the story, but the music that made the films great as did of course the irresitible charm of Tapen Chattopadhyay (Gupi) and Robi Ghosh (Bagha). Sadly, there will be no more Gupi Bagha films for Robi Ghosh is no more and nor is Ray and his brilliant musical scores. It is in these films that his musical genius reached its peak, for the songs of Gupi and Bagha are immortalised in the minds of perhaps every Bengali.

Unfortnately these great films are only available in very poor quality and that too not in a single collection. For some time I have been toying with the idea of enhancing the video of these films. I had earlier uploaded &quot;Goopy Gyne Bagha Byne&quot; and &quot;Hirak Rajar Deshe&quot; in x.254/MKV format and will be uploading &quot;Goopy Bagha Phirey Elo&quot; in a coulple of days, as promised a long time earlier. But the enthusiastic response made me think a little bit more ambitiously. What if I could put all the three together in a single collection? Could I add on a menu, as I had once done earlier for &quot;Satyajit ray Presents&quot; although that was in DivX? Could I fit it in one single DVD disc so people can enjoy it off-line? At the same time could I make it possible to play the menu and the movies on the computer as well? The answer was in the AVCHD/Blu-Ray format and so here is the end result. I believe it is the only AVCHD rip on the net.

